<P>THE MAN OF FEELING: A NOVEL, BY MR. MACKENZIE, OF EDINBURG. AUTHOR OF JULIA DE ROUBIGNE, AND THE MAN OF THE WORLD.</P>
<P>WITH THE SENTIMENTAL SAILOR. A POEM, ORIGINATING FROM ROUSSEAU'S ELOISA.</P>
<Q><L><HI>A maid adorn'd with more than mortal charms</HI></L>
<L><HI>Is held far di&s;tant from my longing arms,</HI></L>
<L><HI>Then can you, friend, forbid my tears to fall?</HI>&mdash;</L>
<L><HI>When in another's arms I view my all</HI></L>
<L><HI>Can I with patience &s;ee my claim o'erthrown</HI></L>
<L><HI>And yield that heart I thought &s;o late my own?</HI></L>
<BIBL>PROPERTIUS.</BIBL></Q>
