<P>THERE are many &s;trange cu&s;toms to be met with in the hi&s;tory of mankind; but the fea&s;t of the dead, or the fea&s;t of &s;ouls, a &s;o|lemn and dreadful fe&s;tival of the Americans is certainly the mo&s;t &s;urpri&s;ing. It is de&s;cribed in almo&s;t too lively colours by the learn|ed <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> in his Meurs de Sauvages. The opening of the tombs; the general di&s;interment of every individual of the nation who <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> &s;ince the la&s;t fe&s;tival of that kind; the putrid dead, digu&s;ting
